Now I'll execute the network_fetcher tool to retrieve data from the API using the default URL parameter.

<tool_call>network_fetcher</tool_call>
```json
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
```

Now I need to execute the data_processing_parser tool to parse the data retrieved by the network_fetcher. Since the validator depends on the parser, I need to run the parser first. I'll use the default input path.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser</tool_call>
```json
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
```

Now I need to execute the data_processing_transformer to convert the JSON data to CSV format. I'll use the default input and output formats.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer</tool_call>
```json
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "csv",
  "options": {}
}
```
